THIRTY-THIRD LEGISLATURE, 2026
STATE OF HAWAII
C.D. 1
A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO AGRICULTURAL GRANT ADMINISTRATION.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that federal agricultural
2 grants provide financial support to Hawaii's agricultural
3 industry. The department of agriculture and biosecurity
4 actively pursues these federal grants and has recently hired a
5 grant writer, whose efforts have yielded great results. Since
6 November 2024, $8,899,450.16 in federal grant funds have been
7 obtained from the United States Department of Agriculture and
8 another $5,285,000 in grants have applications in process. Many
9 of the federal grants being pursued by the department provide
10 for indirect overhead reimbursements or an allowable management
11 fee to reimburse the State for costs associated with management
12 of certain federal grants.
13 The legislature further finds that the establishment of a
14 formal agricultural grant program and a revolving fund would
15 allow the department of agriculture and biosecurity to retain
16 these funds and cover a portion of the program costs. Funds
17 from the revolving fund would be used to search for additional
2026-3358 HB2246 CDl HMSO
