1 grant opportunities, develop program applications to monitor
2 grant execution, ensure compliance with grant requirements, and
3 audit grant expenditures. Moneys in the fund will also be used
4 for consultant services and operational expenses.
5 The purpose of this Act is to establish an agricultural
6 grant program in the department of agriculture and biosecurity
7 and an agricultural grant revolving fund.
8 SECTION 2. Chapter 141, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
9 amended by adding two new sections to part I to be appropriately
10 designated and to read as follows:
11 "§141-A Agricultural grant program; established. (a)
12 There is established in the department of agriculture and
13 biosecurity an agricultural grant program to search for, apply
14 for, and administer federal agricultural grant opportunities
15 that could benefit the Hawaii agricultural industry.
16 (b) The department of agriculture and biosecurity may
17 retain and expend federal indirect overhead reimbursements for
18 grants as determined by the chairperson of the board of
19 agriculture and biosecurity.
20 §141-B Agricultural grant revolving fund. (a) There is
21 established in the state treasury an agricultural grant
