1 revolving fund into which shall be deposited the department of
2 agriculture and biosecurity's share of federal indirect overhead
3 reimbursements, pursuant to section 141-A.
4 (b) Moneys in the agricultural grant revolving fund shall
5 be expended by the department of agriculture and biosecurity to
6 search for discretionary grants, develop program applications to
7 secure additional revenues for the department of agriculture and
8 biosecurity, monitor grant execution, ensure compliance with
9 grant reguirements, and audit grant expenditures. Moneys in the
10 revolving fund may be expended for consultant services and
11 operational expenses, including the hiring of temporary staff.
12 (c) The department of agriculture and biosecurity shall
13 prepare and submit an annual report on the status of the
14 agricultural grant revolving fund to the legislature no later
15 than twenty days prior to the convening of each regular session.
16 The annual report shall include but not be limited to a list of
17 federal agricultural grant applications submitted and grant
18 awards received."
19 SECTION 3. In codifying the new sections added by section
20 2 of this Act, the revisor of statutes shall substitute
